&nbsp;
"This afternoon the president plans to hold a meeting to discuss the measures taken after the terrorist attack. High officials will attend the meeting," said the spokesman for the Russian presidency, Dmitry Peskov. to journalists. It will be a public meeting, he said. "The president continues to be informed by all their services," he added.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Kremlin, who accused Ukraine of providing logistical support to the four suspected attackers arrested, refused to comment on the claim reached by the Isis and believes that there is still no &nbsp; a "sure hypothesis" on the paternity of the atac.
