Peskov also defended the action of Russian security services, which were the subject of harsh criticism on social networks. "The security services work tirelessly and face all threats, all the challenges our country and our society face"; underlined that Russian intelligence services " operate alone" and denied that there is no contact in this sense with Western counterparts. According to the Kremlin spokesman "there is no one city or one country that is completely protected by the threat of terrorism".
&nbsp;
"The fight against terrorism is a permanent process requiring full international cooperation," he said. but he added that at present, in this "period of confrontation, acute to the maximum, is not that there is no cooperation on the whole field, there is no cooperation".
&nbsp;
In his speech to the nation last Saturday, in the first exit to the aftermath of the massacre, President Vladimir Putin did not mention the Islamic State but indicated that the terrorists, when they were captured, were heading towards the Ukrainian border.
<h2>Paris offers more cooperation
The French president, Emmanuel Macron>, has announced that he has offered the Russian authorities "more cooperation" after the massacre in Moscow.
&nbsp;
The head of the Elysée has announced that the Islamic State group Khorasan has tried several times to attack France. The branch of the terrorist group "coinvolto" in the massacre in Moscow made "different attempts" in France, said the French president upon his arrival in Guyana.
&nbsp;
France has raised the level of alert of the Vigipirate anti-terrorism plan after the attack in Moscow claimed by Isis.&nbsp;

